{"article_id":"YokqOeNRqyOZs7D0","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"A tiny Montana company from Interior Secretary Ryan Zinke ' s hometown inked a $ 300 million contract","depth":10},{"id":1,"text":"to help restore electrical power on Puerto Rico ,","depth":10},{"id":2,"text":"according to a report Tuesday .","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"Whitefish Energy ,","depth":11},{"id":4,"text":"which only had two employees","depth":12},{"id":5,"text":"when Hurricane Maria slammed into Puerto Rico on Sept. 20 ,","depth":12},{"id":6,"text":"now has 280 workers on the island ,","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"the majority of whom are subcontractors ,","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"the Washington Post reported .","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"The contract with the Puerto Rico Electric Power Authority is the largest","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"issued so far in the relief effort ,","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"the report said .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"PREPA decided to hire Whitefish","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"instead of activating \" mutual aid \" arrangements","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"it has with other utilities ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"understandings","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"typically used among US power companies","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"to hasten recovery efforts from natural disasters , such as the recent hurricanes in Texas and Florida .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"A month after Maria hit ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"about three-quarters of Puerto Rico ' s 3.4 million residents still are without power .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"A former official at the Energy Department said","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"the selection of Whitefish is \" odd . \"","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"see also","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"Private security mercenaries are now moving into Puerto Rico","depth":4},{"id":24,"text":"The situation is so bad in Puerto Rico","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"that a ...","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"\" The fact","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"that there are so many utilities with experience in this and a huge track record","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"of helping each other out ,","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"it is at least odd why","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"[ the utility ] would go to Whitefish , \"","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"Susan F. Tierney , a former senior official at the Energy Department and state regulatory agencies , told the newspaper .","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"\" I ' m scratching my head wondering","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"how it all adds up . \"","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"Ricardo Ramos , PREPA ' s executive director , has told reporters","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"that Whitefish was chosen","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"because it was the first company \" available to arrive","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"and they were the ones","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"that first accepted the terms and conditions \" of the authority .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"\" The doubts","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"that have been raised about Whitefish ,","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"from my point of view , are completely unfounded , \"","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"he said .","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"\" So the carping by others is unfounded ,","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"and we stand by our work and our commitment to the people of Puerto Rico , \"","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"he told the Washington Post .","depth":7},{"id":46,"text":"Zinke ' s office said","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"the secretary knows Whitefish ' s top executive ,","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"but that ' s not unusual in a town with a population of a little more than 7,000 people .","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"Remains of a shed","depth":4},{"id":50,"text":"scattered over a basketball court after Hurricane Maria near Loiza , Puerto Rico","depth":4},{"id":51,"text":"Reuters","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"Buildings","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"damaged by Hurricane Maria in Lares , Puerto Rico","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"Reuters","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"A damaged home among blown-down trees in San Sebastian , Puerto Rico","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"Reuters","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"The contents of a damaged home are visible","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"as recovery efforts continue","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"following Hurricane Maria near the town of Comerio , Puerto Rico .","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"REUTERS","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"The remains of damaged homes stand next to a cemetery in Morovis , Puerto Rico .","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"REUTERS","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"A truck attempts to pull another vehicle across a flood-damaged roadway near the village of San Lorenzo , Puerto Rico .","depth":14},{"id":64,"text":"REUTERS","depth":15},{"id":65,"text":"The contents of a damaged home near the town of Comerio , Puerto Rico","depth":15},{"id":66,"text":"REUTERS","depth":15},{"id":67,"text":"Residents fill containers with water from a creek near the town of Comerio , Puerto Rico .","depth":15},{"id":68,"text":"REUTERS","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"A landslide-damaged home near Orocovis , Puerto Rico","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"Reuters Reuters","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"Damaged homes near Ciales , Puerto Rico","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"Reuters A damaged home on the edge of a swollen river near Ciales , Puerto Rico","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"Reuters","depth":16},{"id":74,"text":"A bridge shows the effects of a swollen river .","depth":17},{"id":75,"text":"REUTERS","depth":17},{"id":76,"text":"The remains of a highway bridge near Ciales , Puerto Rico","depth":16},{"id":77,"text":"REUTERS","depth":17},{"id":78,"text":"REUTERS","depth":18},{"id":79,"text":"A flood-damaged bridge near Ciales , Puerto Rico","depth":18},{"id":80,"text":"REUTERS","depth":17},{"id":81,"text":"Aluminum roofing twisted and thrown off buildings near San Jose , Puerto Rico","depth":17},{"id":82,"text":"REUTERS","depth":17},{"id":83,"text":"Traffic is diverted","depth":18},{"id":84,"text":"to avoid a flood-damaged bridge near San Jose , Puerto Rico .","depth":18},{"id":85,"text":"Reuters","depth":17},{"id":86,"text":"People inspect the remains of a flood-damaged bridge near the village of San Lorenzo , Puerto Rico .","depth":17},{"id":87,"text":"Reuters","depth":17},{"id":88,"text":"The contents of a damaged home near the town of Comerio , Puerto Rico","depth":17},{"id":89,"text":"Reuters","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"Ad Up Next Close","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"Cops searching for woman in subway slashing","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"This is the woman","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"who police say","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"slashed a stranger ... 20","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"View Slideshow","depth":5},{"id":96,"text":"Back Continue","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"Share this : Facebook","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"It added","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"that Zinke played no role","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"in getting the contract .","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"The House Committee on Natural Resources is looking into PREPA ' s hiring of Whitefish .","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"Related Video","depth":3},{"id":103,"text":"Video length 41 seconds :41","depth":3},{"id":104,"text":"The aftermath on Hurricane Maria in Puerto Rico","depth":3},{"id":105,"text":"The aftermath on Hurricane Maria in Puerto Rico","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":211,"left":207,"right":210,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":207,"left":154,"right":206,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":129,"right":153,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":128,"right":23,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":123,"right":127,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":117,"right":122,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":117,"left":114,"right":116,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":114,"left":108,"right":113,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":10